<font color="#FF0000">COMMENTS ON COMMENTS</font><br>
<tt>Fri Dec 20  6:09:01 US/Eastern 1996
</tt><p>
Eric,<br><br>
Your comments are well spoken. They reflect a reality all too common for most of us. Most people do not have an understanding of the impact of the protestors upon Vietnam Veterans. <br><br>
It would be fitting for some of these people to experience the continuing struggles of many veterans still trying to overcome the physical and psychological effects of the war. Just drop by any VA Hospital! Their protests pale in the light of that stark reality.<br><br>
Chuck,<br><br>
Your quotation for Samual Adams sends a vital message across time. It is unfortunate those words went unheeded when those who protested by running from their country were later given an amnesty to return. <br><br>
They should have been left in Canada, or wherever they went, forever. 
